eNCA Political editor, Vuyo Mvoko has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 7pm on Wednesday on developments in South Africa’s risk-adjusted response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Ramaphosa’s address follows a series of meetings  with the National Coronavirus Command Council. COVID-19: National State of Disaster extended Expectations are that South Africa will move to level 1 lockdown. Last week, the cabinet approved the extension of the COVID-19 National State of Disaster to 15 October. You can catch the address on eNCA #DStv Channel 403 and at eNCA.com